Changing the Features types to decrease the memory usage¶

In [18]:
integer = []
floatt = []
cat=[]
for integerr in data.columns[:-1]:
    if data[integerr].dtype == "int64": integer.append(integerr)
    elif data[integerr].dtype == "float64": floatt.append(integerr)
    elif data[integerr].dtype == "object": cat.append(integerr)
    

data[integer] = data[integer].astype("int32")
data[floatt] = data[floatt].astype("float32")

Encoding the features from categorical data type to numric form for the features selection¶

In [36]:
encoder={}
for col in data.columns:
    data[col]=data[col].astype(str)
    encoder[col]=LabelEncoder()
    data[col]=encoder[col].fit_transform(data[col])
data=data.sample(1000)

Feature Selection Techniques and Methods

Univariate feature selection¶

  • using mutual_info_classif technique to extrcat the most useful features from the data

X=data.drop(columns=['TA'])
y=data['TA']
MiC_M= SelectKBest(mutual_info_classif, k=15)
MiC_M.fit(X, y)
MiC_features = MiC_M.transform(X)
